narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: great class. Italian is a fun and beautiful language.Take it with Chris if you can. He is very helpful and understanding.
I would recommend the course because it is a good language to learn, but I would recommend Annie Ruderman if she is teaching it.
An amazing course of italian where you leave with a good ability to speak italian. I would recommend it to another student, because I felt it really enriched my knowledge of languages and of culture.
Pretty easy-going. The work is constant throughout the semester. I would recommend it. If you want a gentle intro language experience, Italian is the class for you.
Yes definitely. It's a great class.

This was, in my opinion, the most ideal course to have every day. There was never a day when I didn't enjoy the class, and always felt challenged yet confident. The staff were wonderful, the events they organizedwere always fun, and I feel thoroughly confident in my ability to read, write, and speak Italian after taking this course.

I would recommend this language course to anyone. It is fun, exciting, and does not require as much work as other languages. I mean, in what other class do you get to watch movies on "culture days" and throw parties involving sheet cake and oven baked nachos?
